// Slip days
I am using one of my 5 slip days.

// Brief overview
This program uses pipes, polling, and signals to implement basic I/O features. This program comes with a --shell flag, which simulates a shell in a child process by using the fork() and exec() system calls. This allows for communication between the shell and the user input from the keyboard.

